Sri Lanka Isn’t Overheating, Needn’t Change Policy, IMF Says

-- B y   A n u s h a   O n d a a t j i e   a n d   A s a n t h a   S i r i m a n n e
-- 
2011-07-04T10:26:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/sri-lanka-isn-t-overheating-needn-t-change-policy-imf-says.html
Sri Lanka needn’t change its monetary
policy as its economy isn’t facing a problem of overheating,
Koshy Mathai, the International Monetary Fund’s resident
representative, said at a business forum in capital  Colombo 
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
